If you are upgrading your Rails application from an older version of Rails:

Please check your Rails app <span class="k">for</span> <span class="s1">'config.i18n.fallbacks = true'</span><span class="nb">.</span>
If you<span class="s1">'re using I18n (&gt;= 1.1.0) and Rails (&lt; 5.2.2), this should be
'</span>config.i18n.fallbacks <span class="o">=</span> <span class="o">[</span>I18n.default_locale]<span class="s1">'.
If not, fallbacks will be broken in your app by I18n 1.1.x.

If you are starting a NEW Rails application, you can ignore this notice.

For more info see:
https://github.com/svenfuchs/i18n/releases/tag/v1.1.0
$
</span></code></pre></div></div>

<h5 id="6-browse-to-httplocalhost4000">6. Browse to http://localhost:4000</h5>

<p>Open a web browser and go to either:</p>

